The "like workbench" tag actually will make your screen an exact clone of
the user's WB, size, screenmode, colourdepth and all.   It's not much use if
you want a specific size-screenmode.

There is a function called, I think, "BestModeID" where you tell it the
size, mode, and depth you want, and it selects the best match available on
the user's system.  I never tried using this, but maybe David McMinn has an
example?

Another way would be to put up a ScreenMode requester, limiting it to show
only those modes available that match your specs.   There is an example how
to do this in the BeatBox2 prefs program, which is in the archive with the
BeatBox2 source.   This is done using standard OS function calls, not NCS,
but it should be compatable.

